flowRoot.flowPara: An outline is drafted by nominated experts. The outline balances recent scientific developments with government and observer requested issues.
Governments and observer organizations nominate experts as authors. Authors are then approved (?).
Authors prepare the 1st, 2nd and final order draft of the report and Summary for Policymakers (SPM).
Governments and experts review the 1st, 2nd and final drafts of the report and SPM. Authors must address all comments prior to approval.
The report is approved, accepted and published.
A key issue is how to identify and select IPCC authors, while maintaining diversity in nationalities. Text-mining the climate literature can rapidly identify the needed expertise with minimum bias.
Big data tools such as topic modelling and network analysis enable a transparent and comprehensive survey of the literature - enhancing the scientific credibility of the literature scoping stage.
Computational linguistics, data processing & extraction, and other content analysis tools can be applied during the drafting stage to summarise large bodies of texts on similar questions and topics.
The technical support unit (TSU) can work in parallel, tracking references...
Text mining can tag, group and prioritise comments.
